We recommended the following:

The Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the MT to observe the prescribed rules and regulations for all collections and remittances;

The LCE cause the immediate procurement of the needed hardware for the upgrading of the server used by the MTO to avoid system malfunction which often necessitates the manual collection of revenues;

The MT shall strictly enjoin all RCOs, whether using automated or manual collection process, to remit all collections intact daily to the MT, through the LO, and prepare the corresponding RCD on a daily basis; and

The MT shall also ensure that the designated LO strictly performs the required procedures in the verification of collections and AF. Give particular attention to manually collected revenues and ensure that the RCDs are verified against the actual official receipts. The accountable forms shall also be verified as to initial balances on hand, receipts, issues and the ending balances on hand, a physical count of the accountable forms remaining in the custody of the RCO shall be made and the balances reported in the SAAF shall be checked.

The Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the MT to observe the prescribed rules and regulations for all collections and remittances;

The MT shall strictly enjoin all RCOs, whether using automated or manual collection process, to remit all collections intact daily to the MT, through the LO, and prepare the corresponding RCD on a daily basis. In case of manual collections made during non-working days (e.g. in markets, slaughterhouses), the collections shall be remitted immediately on the succeeding working day;

The MTO should require the RCOs to explain in writing the reason for committing consistent delay in remitting collections and institute appropriate sanctions such as relief from duties and filing appropriate administrative actions provided by applicable laws, rules and regulations; and

The LCE shall direct the Municipal Assessor to fast track the updating of the assessed values of the real properties in the version 2.5 of the ETRACS so that said version can already be used in the collection of RPT.

formulate guidelines and policies to set parameters, conditions and limitations on the grant of financial assistance taking into account the nature, circumstances and purpose of each request;

direct the Local Development Council to consider the inclusion in the PPAs of the municipality assistance of similar nature and appropriate funds thereto, if warranted; 

instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to ensure that all grants of assistance and incentives shall be supported with complete and appropriate documentations and;

exercise prudence in the disbursement of funds of the Municipality to ensure that resources are utilized and expended appropriately.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive instruct the:
a. 	inventory committee to conduct of proper inventory taking and render a report thereon in   accordance with COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
b. 	Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer to reconcile their records and furnish the inventory committee a copy thereto to assist the committee in the conduct of the physical count of the PPE;
c.	Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary correction/adjustment in the PPE account   based on the inventory report; and
d.  	Confer with the DPWH Accounting Office on the transfer of infrastructure assets particularly the flood control projects since its maintenance belong to the DPWH and also those projects where the potential benefit will directly accrue to the Virac Water District and the Barangays of Virac as initial and crucial step in facilitating the correction of entries in the books of both the DPWH and the local government unit (LGU) of Virac.

We reiterated our recommendation that:
The Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the MT to observe the prescribed rules and regulations for all collections and remittances;
The MT shall strictly enjoin all RCOs, whether using automated or manual collection process, to remit all collections intact daily to the MT, through the LO, and prepare the corresponding RCD on a daily basis;
The MT shall also ensure that the designated LO strictly performs the required procedures in the verification of collections and AF. The LO shall ensure that the completeness of the accountable forms be verified as to initial balances, receipts, issuances, and ending balances on hand. Physical count of the accountable forms remaining in the custody of the RCO shall be made and the balances reported in the SAAF shall be checked; and
The LCE direct the Municipal Accountant to record the cash shortage under the “Due from Officers and Employees” account to be reported in the Financial Statements as of December 31, 2023.

We recommended the following:
For the operation of the facilities and equipment intended for the solid waste management program, Management should coordinate with the Local Electric Cooperative for the commencement of the upgrading and extension of the existing distribution line. Henceforth, the Municipality shall perform constant follow-ups to ensure prompt action by the Local Electric Cooperative;
For the operation of the animal shelter, the Municipality shall expedite the compliance with and submission of the requirements mandated by the BAI to operationalize the facility;
For the operation of the fish landing, the Local Chief Executive shall direct the MAO to undertake all the necessary measures to fully operationalize the facility.
We also recommended that Management through the Local Development Council to carefully and judiciously plan the developmental projects to be charged to the 20% DF to ensure optimization of resources and for beneficiaries to attain maximum benefit pursuant to Section 2 of PD 1445 and Section 305g of RA 1760.

We recommended that Management:
Strengthen the LGU’s planning and preparatory procurement activities particularly its detailed engineering investigation, surveys and designs to minimize suspensions and delays in the implementation process;
Require the Municipal Engineering Office to submit the aforementioned lacking documents to support the variation order issued for the said project;
Require the Municipal Engineering Office to submit justification on the request for time extension for the completion of the project despite the fact that the Punong Barangay of Sogod Tibgao issued certification already to the effect road right of way issues had been resolved; and
Ensure that all changes/revisions made to contracts for the implementation of infrastructure projects are adequately supported by required documentations as prescribed under Item 1.5 of Annex E of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and COA Circular No. 2012-001.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Require an explanation from the heads of offices on the absence in the APP or the Supplemental APP of the specific appropriation for the purchase of airline tickets;
Direct all department heads/end users to include in their Project Procurement Management Plan (PPMP) all acquisitions of airline tickets planned for the year and submit the same to the BAC Secretariat for consolidation and basis for preparation of the APP;
Ensure that no procurement shall be authorized and undertaken unless it is in accordance with an approved APP or supplemental APP; and
Instruct all officials and employees to purchase airline tickets directly from commercial airlines and service providers as provided under Section V, Item b of Annex H of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184.

direct the Municipal Treasurer to conduct an inventory of unreleased checks to ensure that the long outstanding checks were truly issued to the payees; if checks were still in custody of the MTO, payees should be informed of their unclaimed checks for replacement if warranted;

require the Municipal Treasurer to maintain a logbook for checks issued with payees signing thereon upon receipt for monitoring purposes; and

direct the Municipal Accounting Office to reclassify unclaimed stale checks to Accounts Payable to adjust both the payables and the Cash in Bank account balances.

require the MHO to render a report to the Municipal Accountant on the receipt, issuance, and balances of vaccines directly received from outside sources;

require the reconciliation of the vaccines received by the MHO as against the record of issuances by the PHO to LGU Virac; and

direct the Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the MHO, to determine the full cost of ending inventory of vaccines as at year end, if any and henceforth recognize and record future receipts and issuances of the same.

direct the Municipal Accountant to substantiate the balance of the RHU-affiliation fund and together with the Municipal Health Officer recommend measures to improve its utilization particularly now that regular school activities are in full swing;

look into the LHB Resolution No. 4 for immediate endorsement to the Sangguniang Bayan of Virac for adoption and enactment;

instruct the BAC to facilitate the procurement of the items charged from the PCSO funds; and 

cause the return of the prior years’ unexpended balances to the source agencies.

We recommended that Management:

Formulate and adopt written guidelines and polices in hiring of JO workers with an end view of limiting the number of hired JO workers based on actual need of the Office; 

Direct the HRMO to control, monitor and update JO records every month;


Require the Offices to submit a schedule of the number of additional personnel to complement the workload of regular personnel indicating the functions to be performed.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct: 

the MT to request from the servicing banks the concerned credit and debit advices/memos as basis of the MAO to record bank transactions;

the concerned offices/employees to exert extensive efforts in retrieving/locating the remaining unrecorded check disbursements for immediate submission to the MAO to effect the necessary adjustments;

the concerned personnel in the Office of the Mayor to return immediately the paid DVs for AICS to MTO for immediate recording in the cashbook and transmittal thereof to the MAO to avoid unrecorded check disbursements; and

the Municipal Accountant (MA) to record the identified book reconciling items and thereafter furnish the Office of the Auditor copies of the JEV taking up the adjustments.

We recommended that the LCE require:

the GSO to initiate the provision of stock room for proper storage of inventories;

the MA and the GSO to coordinate in implementing the perpetual inventory method of recording supplies and materials;

the GSO to prepare the SSMIs supported with RIS for supplies and materials issued and the MA to prepare JEV as supported by SSMIs and RIS submitted by the GSO to record issuance of supplies and materials; and

the Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory of supplies and materials semestrally and submit the Physical Inventory Report to the AT as required in Section 124, Volume 1 of the MNGAs.

We recommended that the LCE:

Direct the MT to work back on the CYs 2018 and 2019 transactions to compute the tax credits as of December 31, 2019 and maintain schedule of taxpayers with  tax credit balances;

Direct the Municipal Assessor to ensure completeness of schedule of market values in the E-TRACS for both CY 2018 and CY 2013 revisions;

Maximize the use of the E-TRACS by incorporating the necessary updates and adjustments to adopt the suspension of the CY 2018 schedule of market values, subject to internal control policies; and

Consider hiring or outsourcing of Information Technology Specialist to perform maintenance activities of the ETRACS and ensure coordination among the MAsO and MTO in the use thereof.

We recommended that Management: 

Submit immediately the information and documents required by the EMB Regional Office No. V without prejudice to immediate closure and rehabilitation of the existing open dumpsite as directed by the same office per its letter dated January 12, 2020;  

Prepare the proposed sanitary landfill to accommodate solid wastes upon the imminent closure of the dumpsite.  Such immediate action is necessary to address if not prevent, detrimental ecological issues and their effects on human health and to the environment;

Prepare a comprehensive work plan for SWM operation indicating all activities to be performed with corresponding budget per activity.  This would more or less guide the LGU in the implementation and in assessing the SWM operations;

Institutionalize the SWM program by creating a separate office with separate budget and with permanent appointed official as Head of Office to run its affairs.

We recommended that Management should strive for total implementation of projects by ensuring that:

Pre-engineering works such as identification of definite project sites should be done and integrated in project proposals prior to submission to the concerned NGAs for consideration; 

Be decisive in the utilization of cash awards/winnings for social amelioration programs; 

Refund immediately unutilized fund transfers as required under the Memorandum of Agreement, and 

Follow-ups on early releases of project funds be done in accordance with the approved timelines in the implementation thereof.

