We recommended the following:

The Local Chief Executive (LCE) to require the Inventory Committee to conduct complete physical inventory of PPE including infrastructure assets and render report thereon as required under Section 124, Chapter 7, Volume I of the NGAS Manual. The progress of the inventory taking should be monitored by the LCE;

Thereafter, the Committee, the General Services Office (GSO) and the Municipal Accounting Office (MAO) reconcile all the inventory reports with the recorded PPE in the books of accounts; 

Require the designated Property Officer to maintain property cards and update them periodically to aid in the conduct of physical count and to solve or minimize the perennial problem of unreconciled accounting and property records; and

The Committee should be cautioned that failure to perform their duties as Chairman and Members of the Inventory Committee may be a valid ground for filing of administrative charges for gross neglect of duty.

We recommended that the LCE to direct the:

Designated GS Officer to consolidate the weekly Requisition Issue slips (RIS) in the SSMI for CY 2019 and the previous years’ transactions, and submit the same to the MA together with the original copies of the RIS;

MA to prepare the necessary JEVs based on the submitted SSMIs and record the expenditures under the Prior Period Adjustment account pursuant to Section 121 of NGAS Manual, Volume I.

We recommended that the LCE:

Require the Supplier to deliver immediately the two units six-wheeler dump-trucks with correct specifications so that the same could be used in garbage collection activities of the SWM program and reinforce the aging garbage fleet of the LGU;

Impose liquidated damages to the transaction and deduct the same in final payment;

Negotiate with the DBP for condonation of interest for the unutilized loan, if possible; and

In similar situation in the future, ensure that before requesting for the release of loan proceeds, see to it that specifications conform to the contract thus, a valid obligation exists and benefits from financing program will be enjoyed without paying interest.

